Isolate CPUs with grubby 
Grubby is a command line tool which allows you to manipulate your grub bootloader. More about this can be found here 

#To isolate CPUs 
 

grubby --args="isolcpus=2-4" --update-kernel=ALL 
reboot 

 

 
#To revert change 

grubby --remove-args="isolcpus=2-4" --update-kernel=ALL 
reboot 
